-- Dassault Aviation to Open China Unit in 2012, Figaro Says
-- B y   M e l i s s a   P o z s g a y
-- 2012-05-14T05:34:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/dassault-aviation-to-open-china-unit-in-2012-figaro-says.html
Dassault Aviation SA (AM)  is opening a
unit in China that will employ 25 people by the end of this
year, Le Figaro reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Charles Edelstenne.  The unit will be based in Beijing and be up and running in
around the third quarter, the newspaper said. Dassault Aviation
expects to deliver 12 Falcon jets in China this year, compared
with eight in 2011, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Melissa Pozsgay in Paris at 
 mpozsgay@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
